HELP=$"
cpref	none	 	spells with their cpref
cpref	spell file	 	select compile method for spell
cpref	spell	 	return to default cpref for spell"

LONG=$"
cpref is an abbreviation for compile preference file.
Compiler preference files can be created using sorcery.
Typically, they export CFLAGS, CXXFLAGS, and LDFLAGS
Those environment variables tend to effect how software
is compiled and linked.

However, only the default cpref is applied automatically.
To have a spell compile using the non default cpref
then the cpref command must be used to indicate that spell
should compile only using the specified cpref.

Typically, the cpref command would be used in order to
compile certain software with debug information.
Normal optimized compiling and linking of software
does not contain debug information because debug
information makes object files large and slower."

param(){
 if (( $# == 0 )); then show_grimoire; return; fi
 find $CPREF_DIR -type f -printf '%f\n'
}

run(){
 if [[ -z $1 ]]; then
  grep -r "" $CPREF_LOGS 2>/dev/null |
  basenames | tr  ':' '\t' | column -t
 elif [[ -z $2 ]]
 then rm   -f     $CPREF_LOGS/$1
 else mkdir_p     $CPREF_LOGS
      echo "$2" > $CPREF_LOGS/$1
 fi
}
